Note: In the answer, "autumn" and "fall" are used interchangeably in some regions, but they both refer to the season when leaves typically change color and fall off deciduous trees. "Photosynthesis" is the process by which leaves convert sunlight into energy for the tree. "Leaf litter" refers to the layer of fallen leaves on the ground, and "decomposition" is the process by which those leaves break down and return nutrients to the soil.
